An SOP, or Standard Operating Procedure, is a document that outlines a specific process or procedure used within an organization. It is designed to ensure consistency and efficiency in the execution of tasks and processes.
Why is it important to write an SOP?
Writing an SOP is important for several reasons. Firstly, it helps ensure that everyone in the organization is following the same procedures, reducing errors and inconsistencies.
